- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the use of social media platforms for a social movement.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of social media on a societal issue.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper may discuss the technical aspects of analyzing social media data.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the computational challenges of analyzing large amounts of social media data.
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also a possibility as the paper analyzes the behavior and reactions of social media users in response to a societal issue.
